Responsibilities:
To source and manage 3rd party products and services in a timely manner to ensure material/ services availability for Project and MRO orders.
Provide technical support to hub/sub and Rep in interpretation and understanding of 3rd party suppliersâ€™ material specifications (Specification, Drawings, etc) and resolving any discrepancies.
Work closely with 3rd party suppliers in the development and improvement of products, process and materials specifications as well as developing action plans to improve: 1) Quality, 2) Delivery LT, and 3) Service Level performance.
Provide support in the implementation of Buyout Commodity Sourcing programs like Best Cost Country Sourcing, Cost Containment, Cost Reductions and others.
Requirements:
Degree in Electrical/Electronics, Mechanical Engineering or equivalent with 1 to 3 years working experience in Supply Chain in a manufacturing environment.
Must possess strong interpersonal & communication skills and strong customer focus.
Sourcing experience with oil and gas industry background preferred.